<div class="policies-page">
  <div class="container py-5">
    <header class="policies-header text-center mb-5">
      <h1 class="policies-title">Policies</h1>
      <p class="policies-lead">
        Review Digify BPO workplace policies in one place. Select a policy below to expand its full guidance.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="policy-accordion">
      <details class="policy-item">
        <summary>
          {{#if settings.drug_policy_icon_url}}
            <img class="policy-card-icon" src="{{settings.drug_policy_icon_url}}" alt="" role="presentation">
          {{/if}}
          <span>Drug and Alcohol Policy</span>
          <span class="toggle-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </summary>
        <div class="policy-content">
          <p>
            Digify BPO maintains a zero-tolerance approach to working under the influence of alcohol, illegal substances, or misused prescription medication.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Associates must report to duty fit for work and remain substance-free for the entire shift, including breaks.</li>
            <li>Random and for-cause testing may be conducted; refusal to comply is treated as a positive result.</li>
            <li>Any possession, distribution, or sale of illegal substances on company premises results in immediate disciplinary action.</li>
            <li>Team members who suspect a colleague is impaired should escalate to the Site Lead or HR partner.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="policy-item">
        <summary>
          {{#if settings.clean_desk_policy_icon_url}}
            <img class="policy-card-icon" src="{{settings.clean_desk_policy_icon_url}}" alt="" role="presentation">
          {{/if}}
          <span>Clean Desk Policy</span>
          <span class="toggle-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </summary>
        <div class="policy-content">
          <p>
            Security of client data depends on keeping shared work areas free from physical and digital clutter at all times.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Lock or log out of all devices whenever stepping away, even for short breaks.</li>
            <li>Store notebooks, printed tickets, or reference materials in assigned lockers at the end of shift.</li>
            <li>Shred documents with customer information immediately after use; never place them in regular trash bins.</li>
            <li>Do not attach passwords, tokens, or personal identifiers to monitors, keyboards, or walls.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="policy-item">
        <summary>
          {{#if settings.locker_policy_icon_url}}
            <img class="policy-card-icon" src="{{settings.locker_policy_icon_url}}" alt="" role="presentation">
          {{/if}}
          <span>Locker Policy for Contact Centre Agents</span>
          <span class="toggle-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </summary>
        <div class="policy-content">
          <p>
            Lockers help protect personal belongings and sensitive work materials while on-site.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Each agent receives one assigned locker; keep it locked whenever not retrieving items.</li>
            <li>Only company-approved padlocks are permitted. Facility staff may remove any other locks for security checks.</li>
            <li>Food, liquids, or perishable goods are not allowed inside lockers to maintain cleanliness.</li>
            <li>Report lost keys or access issues to Facilities immediately so the lock can be replaced.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="policy-item">
        <summary>
          {{#if settings.pci_policy_icon_url}}
            <img class="policy-card-icon" src="{{settings.pci_policy_icon_url}}" alt="" role="presentation">
          {{/if}}
          <span>PCI Compliance Policy</span>
          <span class="toggle-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </summary>
        <div class="policy-content">
          <p>
            Protecting cardholder data is essential to maintaining PCI DSS compliance across CX operations.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Never record card numbers, CVVs, or expiration dates in chat logs, notes, or local storage.</li>
            <li>Only access payment systems with approved, segmented accounts and multifactor authentication.</li>
            <li>Report suspected data exposure to the PCI Compliance Officer within 15 minutes of discovery.</li>
            <li>Follow secure desk proceduresâ€”no mobile phones, cameras, or personal devices in PCI-zoned areas.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="policy-item">
        <summary>
          {{#if settings.smoking_policy_icon_url}}
            <img class="policy-card-icon" src="{{settings.smoking_policy_icon_url}}" alt="" role="presentation">
          {{/if}}
          <span>Smoking Policy</span>
          <span class="toggle-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </summary>
        <div class="policy-content">
          <p>
            Smoking, vaping, and e-cigarette use are regulated to keep indoor workspaces clean and compliant with local ordinances.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Smoking is prohibited inside all Digify BPO facilities and within 6 meters of building entrances.</li>
            <li>Use only designated smoking areas during authorized break times to avoid penalties.</li>
            <li>Dispose of cigarette waste in the receptacles provided; littering is subject to citation.</li>
            <li>Repeated non-compliance may lead to loss of break privileges or formal disciplinary action.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="policy-item">
        <summary>
          {{#if settings.harassment_policy_icon_url}}
            <img class="policy-card-icon" src="{{settings.harassment_policy_icon_url}}" alt="" role="presentation">
          {{/if}}
          <span>Sexual Harassment Policy</span>
          <span class="toggle-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </summary>
        <div class="policy-content">
          <p>
            Digify BPO upholds a zero-tolerance stance against sexual harassment or misconduct, regardless of role or location.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Harassment includes unwelcome advances, suggestive comments, offensive jokes, or any behavior that creates a hostile environment.</li>
            <li>Report incidents immediately to HR, your manager, or via the confidential hotline. Reports may be anonymous.</li>
            <li>Retaliation against any individual who files or supports a report is strictly prohibited.</li>
            <li>Confirmed violations result in disciplinary measures, up to and including termination and legal escalation.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </details>
    </section>
  </div>
</div>
